				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was referring to the augment, not the item. And Magelo's dont' really mean crap to me, I'd like to see it in reality - I still don't believe its possible. That being said - I'll give it another go to go back to pet feasability:
<br />

<br />
Possible Pet AA revision: Keep the four basic pet enhancers we have now (Durability, Agility, Fury, Alacrity) but make it so you can only choose two of them. This would be mutually exclusive. Anyone that's read this far down knows why I think pets should have mutually exclusive increases, so I won't go into that.
<br />

<br />
Possible Focus Revision: Availability, of course, but make specialized focuses. Some concentrate on defense, some offense, some both. 
<br />

<br />
Possible Buff Revision: A spell that doesn't stack with burnout, but makes the pet a tanking machine. Burnout = Dps. Whateverelse = Defense.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">For example, going from bazaar/1groupable gear to Anguish gear then casters gain around 20% + a larger mana pool, melee gain > 50% in weapons alone and thats discounting effects such as Ferocity and Cleave (though they are obtained via bazaar or single groups nowadays though at a huge price) </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
For the hell of it - I'll address this.
<br />

<br />
The biggest difference between Melee's and Casters is (in my mind) one of two things:
<br />

<br />
1) Melee's don't depend on something expendable (mana) for DPS. They depend on pressing "attack". 
<br />
2) Melee's have a floor for their melee dps. Melee dps does not typically go below that floor, where Casters do. 
<br />

<br />
First: Melee's depend only on being alive and having haste - both which debateably can't run out if you play well.  Casters can not be effective in raid situations without expending large amounts of mana - which leads to being OOM. Our damage potential expires where melee's don't. 
<br />

<br />
Second: Child of Wind, as a melee, will never hit for 11 damage. Why is this? It has a floor that, depending on the focus, hovers around 30. Your pet will either miss entirely, or hit for 30-110 damage. I personally have used Blade Strike in a raid and criticalled for 40. Resists are comparable to the "dodge/riposte/parry" thing for melee's, so why are we further hindered by the lack of a floor? 
<br />

<br />
If you want a DPS upgrade for nukes ask for a floor compareable to melee's (% based).  Myself, I'd like an increase in damage per second through pets, so that our pet does about 1/2 the total DPS we can produce.  Hence why I even began this post <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
