<br />
'Anguish' Mage: 45% DD foci, 20% mana pres, 23% spell haste, 11000 manapool, FT20, click item from Tacvi, 9 mana regen from tacvi ear click and 3 mana regen from Shield of Dreams.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Sheesh -- you all are still whining about this. Its an "apples to apples" comparison. Best of the Bazaar vs. Best of Raiding. 
<br />

<br />
Here's the bottom line on it:
<br />

<br />
DD focus -- 45% vs. 25% -- 10% on average
<br />
Pet focus -- less than 5%
<br />
MP focus -- 15% (Jolum's) vs. 20% -- 2.5% on average
<br />
FT20 -- achievable by either
<br />

<br />

<br />
For situations other than drawn out boss takedowns, around 10-15% difference.
<br />

<br />
A mana regen clickie is good for what, 6-8 mana/sec against 60-120 mana/sec? Throw in another 5-10%.
<br />

<br />
Mana pool <span style="font-style: italic">only </span>comes into play when you are in a battle long enough that it is completely drained. (Grouping is generally about sustained damage. Soloing I remember running out of HP, pet's then mine, long before mana.)
<br />

<br />
Not only are these differences relatively small, but the line that says "Pet focus" is the most depressing.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
<br />
"Nothing to see here. Move along. Move along." 
<br />
"These are not the droids you are looking for."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
