				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Kirium_Veeshan wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Actually those figures are based on Zacatac's magelo </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How did I get dragged into this?   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_shifty.gif" alt="Anxious" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
My mana pool, with enchanter buff, is about 6700.
<br />

<br />
Because I don't raid much, and don't have raid gear, I'll never have the huge HP/MANA of the other 70 magicians. 
<br />

<br />
And, therefore, <span style="font-weight: bold">I've gone for FT gear as my primary goal</span>.  Currently at FT-21 actually, and I banked my solstice earring or it would be 22, and also sold my Viscid Slime Gloves, or it would be FT-26.   And that's with only the 1 augment (FT-1).    
<br />

<br />
So yes, it is possible to hit FT-20 if you really want to spend the money in <span style="font-weight: bold">bazaar</span> or do the <span style="font-weight: bold">quests</span> I've done (8th shawl, Droga neck, Oracle robe, etc).  My goal now is to have an upgrade with FT (2nd OoW bracer maybe) so I can lose something else without dropping below 20.
<br />

<br />
My normal set up=
<br />
Phantom Shield (9 mana/tick)
<br />
FT-20
<br />
KEI (or better) (14+/mana tick)
<br />
MC-3 (3 mana/tick)
<br />
Elemental draw (3 mana/tick)
<br />
Phylactery (+2 hp/mana per tick)
<br />

<br />
Adds up to 51 mana/tick.  When I'm on a horse for med bonus it's about 76, and toss in T-rods (3-4 mana/tick net when used regularly), you're about 80/mana tick when medding. 
<br />

<br />
Like Lofwyr said, I'm not the "average" bazaar mage.  But <span style="font-weight: bold">the title still fits</span>.  Just like many of you with 8k HP and 10k mana pools aren't the "average" raider.
<br />

<br />
The big difference, in my opinion, is the DD Focus items/spell haste items/mana preservation items, etc. that make it possible to do more DPS, and for a longer period of time, than I could do.  Plus I still use DPoC for pet focus. . .<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
<br />
"1450 Club" Tradeskiller</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Zacatac on Tue Mar 15, 2005 6:47 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
